But she had gonewhile he yet spake, she had left
the room and the houseScipio closely attending her.
The feebleness of age seemed no longer to oppress the
aged man. He rushed after the daughter of his heart
with much of the vigour of youth, and with all the
fearlessness
of a proper manhood. In that moment her worth
was conspicuous, in his forgetfulness of all fear and
feebleness
.
He heeded not the cries and the clamour
